About

Ngành Hiệp Sĩ (the Knights of Eucharist)’s motto is “Dấn thân!”, meaning “Self-Sacrifice!”. This division wears brown scarves, representing the earth where the blood of Vietnamese martyrs was spilled, demonstrating valor, love of country, and love of God. This division consists of members from ages 16 to 17 years old who comprise two levels: Levels 1 and 2.
